--------FRIDAY NIGHT FUNKIN || Meek Engine--------
VERSION 0.5.0
DEVELOPMENT STATUS: ACTIVE

Play and create your own mods for Friday Night Funkin' with this editor! You can also grab a friend and compete with eachother with VS Mode, this mode can be enabled in the options menu!

----------------------------------------------------------------------
FEATURES:
CHARACTER EDITOR
CHART EDITOR
WEEK EDITOR
STAGE EDITOR
JSON COMPILER
CUSTOM ANIMATIONS
VS MODE
ANY FPS SUPPORT
---------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTRUCTIONS AND CONTROLS:
(GUIDE WILL BE POSTED SOON)
- To activate the editor, go inside the project, and go to the sprite that's called "Go Here!" (name already says it so uhh) and click the green circle, this'll activate the editor. To disable the editor, click the red circle!

- To add a character, go into the editor menu and open the character editor, click on "add/delete chars". Then click on the "+" button and enter the name of your character. now go into the project itself and go to the "CHARS" sprite. go into the costumes and name your costume "<charName><animation>1" for example: MeekIdle1, Meekleft1, Meekup1 etc etc.
now go into the character editor again and adjust the positions. (don't forget to go into the icon sprite and also add your icon!)

- To add a song, go into the editor menu and open the song editor, click on "add a song" and once again, hit the plus and enter your song's name. Don't forget to add your song in the "SONG" sprite! it MUST be named "<songName>_Inst" or "<songName>_Voices" (if you don't have any vocals, then that's fine, just name your song <songName>_Inst)
to chart the song you click on "edit a song" in the song editor menu. and select your song. have fun charting! ( DON'T FORGET TO PRESS UPDATE AND SAVE YOUR PROJECT! )

- To add a week, go into the editor menu and select  "WEEK EDITOR" and uh yeah, i think it's pretty simple from there.

- To add an intro text, open the "MENU INTRO TEXTS" list, now add your two texts, seperated by two dashes
like so "example--example". i'd suggest you keep it short

- To compile a JSON file, go into the editor menu, and select "SONG EDITOR", now click "COMPILE JSON"
there's also a tutorial when you start it up. you import your .json file and let it compile. you can either test your song (recommended) or add the song. 

CONTROLS:
- press 7 to open the chart editor
- enter to confirm
- arrow keys to select
- B to go back

------------------------------------------------------------------------
CREDITS:
- the Friday Night Funkin' team!
- @AwezomeXD for the girlfriend and dad vector
- PhantomArcade for the original art
- Kawaii Sprite for the songs
- Ninjamuffin for the original game
- Hydra on youtube for the VS Mode menu track

ALL CODING DONE BY ME
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
CHANGE LOG:
VERSION 0.4.5 ( 4-15-2022 )
- Meek Engine official release

VERSION 0.5.0 ( 6-25-2022 )
- Fixed character system along with character switching
- [ MINOR ] Fixed JSON compiler issues
- [ MINOR ] Renamed "better input" to "ghost tapping"
- Added Stage editor
- Implemented VS mode
- Improved chart editor

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Made by @Meekaryo
PLEASE report any bugs, thanks! :)

SONG sprite - lets you import your instrumental and vocals of a song. (if you don't have a vocal version, don't worry. just import the whole song for the instrumental then.)

to add a new song, make a new list and name it to whatever you like. but remember the song name (i'd suggest you name it #song.<your song name>)

to make the song appear on the freeplay menu, go to the "-SONG LIST-" list, and add your song name there
